text: Thryptomene stapfii is a shrub species in the family Myrtaceae that is endemic to Western Australia. The shrub is found in a small area the Mid West region of Western Australia between Geraldton and Northampton. ==References== stapfii Category:Endemic flora of Western Australia Category:Rosids of Western Australia Category:Vulnerable flora of Australia Category:Plants described in 2014 Category:Taxa named by Barbara Lynette Rye Category:Taxa named by Malcolm Eric Trudgen
